FBIS3-12772 "drnes043_r_94009" FBIS-NES-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 India Naval Exercises Conducted With Russian Ships BK0203133894 Delhi THE HINDUSTAN TIMES in English 21 Feb 94 p 32 BK0203133894 Delhi THE HINDUSTAN TIMES Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] New Delhi, Feb 20 (UNI) -- Indian and Russian Naval ships conducted a two-day exercise during a goodwill visit by three Russian ships to Bombay this week. The exercise was conducted between Indian Naval ships 'Ganga' a frigate, and Ranvir, a destroyer, and Russian ship Admiral Vinogradov, an anti-submarine destroyer. Such bilateral exercises have been undertaken by the Indian navy in the past also with warships of the Indian Ocean Littoral States and friendly countries, official sources today said. The other Russian ships included a landing ship L. Vilkov and a merchant tanker V. Kolechitskiy.
